  30:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****       The LPTIM HAL driver can be used as follows:
  31:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  32:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****       (#)Initialize the LPTIM low level resources by implementing the
  33:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****         HAL_LPTIM_MspInit():
  34:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Enable the LPTIM interface clock using __HAL_RCC_LPTIMx_CLK_ENABLE().
  35:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) In case of using interrupts (e.g. HAL_LPTIM_PWM_Start_IT()):
  36:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) Configure the LPTIM interrupt priority using HAL_NVIC_SetPriority().
  37:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) Enable the LPTIM IRQ handler using HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ().
  38:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) In LPTIM IRQ handler, call HAL_LPTIM_IRQHandler().
  39:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  40:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****       (#)Initialize the LPTIM HAL using HAL_LPTIM_Init(). This function
  41:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          configures mainly:
  42:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) The instance: LPTIM1, LPTIM2, LPTIM3, LPTIM4, LPTIM5 or LPTIM6.
  43:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Clock: the counter clock.
  44:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) Source   : it can be either the ULPTIM input (IN1) or one of
  45:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****                               the internal clock; (APB, LSE, LSI or CSI).
  46:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) Prescaler: select the clock divider.
  47:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++)  UltraLowPowerClock : To be used only if the ULPTIM is selected
  48:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****                as counter clock source.
  49:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) Polarity:   polarity of the active edge for the counter unit
  50:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****                                if the ULPTIM input is selected.
  51:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) SampleTime: clock sampling time to configure the clock glitch
  52:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****                                filter.
  53:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Trigger: How the counter start.
  54:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) Source: trigger can be software or one of the hardware triggers.
  55:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) ActiveEdge : only for hardware trigger.
  56:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****              (+++) SampleTime : trigger sampling time to configure the trigger
  57:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****                                 glitch filter.
  58:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) OutputPolarity : 2 opposite polarities are possible.
  59:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) UpdateMode: specifies whether the update of the autoreload and
  60:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****               the compare values is done immediately or after the end of current
  61:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****               period.
  62:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Input1Source: Source selected for input1 (GPIO or comparator output).
  63:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Input2Source: Source selected for input2 (GPIO or comparator output).
  64:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****               Input2 is used only for encoder feature so is used only for LPTIM1 instance.
  65:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  66:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****       (#)Six modes are available:
  67:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  68:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) PWM Mode: To generate a PWM signal with specified period and pulse,
  69:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          call HAL_LPTIM_PWM_Start() or HAL_LPTIM_PWM_Start_IT() for interruption
  70:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          mode.
  71:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  72:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) One Pulse Mode: To generate pulse with specified width in response
  73:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          to a stimulus, call HAL_LPTIM_OnePulse_Start() or
  74:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          HAL_LPTIM_OnePulse_Start_IT() for interruption mode.
  75:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  76:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Set once Mode: In this mode, the output changes the level (from
  77:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          low level to high level if the output polarity is configured high, else
  78:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          the opposite) when a compare match occurs. To start this mode, call
  79:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          HAL_LPTIM_SetOnce_Start() or HAL_LPTIM_SetOnce_Start_IT() for
  80:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          interruption mode.
  81:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  82:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Encoder Mode: To use the encoder interface call
  83:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          HAL_LPTIM_Encoder_Start() or HAL_LPTIM_Encoder_Start_IT() for
  84:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          interruption mode. Only available for LPTIM1 instance.
  85:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  86:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Time out Mode: an active edge on one selected trigger input rests
ARM GAS  C:\Users\DELL\AppData\Local\Temp\ccgJ6U9P.s 			page 3


  87:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          the counter. The first trigger event will start the timer, any
  88:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          successive trigger event will reset the counter and the timer will
  89:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          restart. To start this mode call HAL_LPTIM_TimeOut_Start_IT() or
  90:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          HAL_LPTIM_TimeOut_Start_IT() for interruption mode.
  91:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  92:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          (++) Counter Mode: counter can be used to count external events on
  93:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          the LPTIM Input1 or it can be used to count internal clock cycles.
  94:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          To start this mode, call HAL_LPTIM_Counter_Start() or
  95:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****          HAL_LPTIM_Counter_Start_IT() for interruption mode.
  96:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  97:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
  98:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****       (#) User can stop any process by calling the corresponding API:
  99:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****           HAL_LPTIM_Xxx_Stop() or HAL_LPTIM_Xxx_Stop_IT() if the process is
 100:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****           already started in interruption mode.
 101:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
 102:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****       (#) De-initialize the LPTIM peripheral using HAL_LPTIM_DeInit().
 103:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
 104:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     *** Callback registration ***
 105:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   =============================================
 106:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   [..]
 107:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   The compilation define  USE_HAL_LPTIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 108:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 109:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   [..]
 110:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   Use Function HAL_LPTIM_RegisterCallback() to register a callback.
 111:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   HAL_LPTIM_RegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 112:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   the Callback ID and a pointer to the user callback function.
 113:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   [..]
 114:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   Use function HAL_LPTIM_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the
 115:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   default weak function.
 116:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   HAL_LPTIM_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 117:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 118:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   [..]
 119:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   These functions allow to register/unregister following callbacks:
 120:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
 121:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback         : LPTIM Base Msp Init Callback.
 122:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback       : LPTIM Base Msp DeInit Callback.
 123:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) CompareMatchCallback    : Compare match Callback.
 124:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) AutoReloadMatchCallback : Auto-reload match Callback.
 125:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) TriggerCallback         : External trigger event detection Callback.
 126:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) CompareWriteCallback    : Compare register write complete Callback.
 127:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) AutoReloadWriteCallback : Auto-reload register write complete Callback.
 128:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) DirectionUpCallback     : Up-counting direction change Callback.
 129:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) DirectionDownCallback   : Down-counting direction change Callback.
 130:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) UpdateEventCallback     : Update event detection Callback.
 131:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****     (+) RepCounterWriteCallback : Repetition counter register write complete Callback.
 132:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
 133:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   [..]
 134:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   By default, after the Init and when the state is HAL_LPTIM_STATE_RESET
 135:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   all interrupt callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 136:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   examples HAL_LPTIM_TriggerCallback(), HAL_LPTIM_CompareMatchCallback().
 137:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
 138:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   [..]
 139:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are reset to the legacy weak
 140:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   functionalities in the Init/DeInit only when these callbacks are null
 141:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   (not registered beforehand). If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the Init/DeInit
 142:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 143:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\DELL\AppData\Local\Temp\ccgJ6U9P.s 			page 4


 144:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   [..]
 145:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_LPTIM_STATE_READY state only.
 146:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 147:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   in HAL_LPTIM_STATE_READY or HAL_LPTIM_STATE_RESET state,
 148:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 149:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 150:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   using HAL_LPTIM_RegisterCallback() before calling DeInit or Init function.
 151:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
 152:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   [..]
 153:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_LPTIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 154:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 155:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   are set to the corresponding weak functions.
 156:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
 157:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   @endverbatim
 158:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   ******************************************************************************
 159:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c ****   */
 160:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** 
 161:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** /* Includes ------------------------------------------------------------------*/
 162:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_lptim.c **** #include "stm32h5xx_hal.h"
